    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 8,
    "last_activity_date" : 1490020688,
    "creation_date" : 1490020688,
    "answer_id" : 42906441,
    "question_id" : 3489543,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Another quicker option to call things (like DialogBoxes and MessageBoxes and creating separate threads for not-thread safe methods) would be to use the Lamba Expression </p>\n\n<pre><code>  new Thread(() -&gt; {\n                      \"code here\"\n            }).start();\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1322392,
      "reputation" : 7559,
      "user_id" : 1690078,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 67,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/34cd353216b1a04b89853c96ab22eab2?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Clyde",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1690078/clyde"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1511303988,
    "creation_date" : 1511303988,
    "answer_id" : 47423955,
    "question_id" : 3489543,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>To achieve this with RxJava 2.x you can use:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Completable.fromAction(this::dowork).subscribeOn(Schedulers.io().subscribe();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The <code>subscribeOn()</code> method specifies which scheduler to run the action on - RxJava has several predefined schedulers, including <code>Schedulers.io()</code> which has a thread pool intended for I/O operations, and <code>Schedulers.computation()</code> which is intended for CPU intensive operations.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 9490046,
      "reputation" : 4441,
      "user_id" : 7055206,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 56,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/a5b6821435a888e63aff6070844120a3?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "k13i",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7055206/k13i"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 20,
    "last_activity_date" : 1563873872,
    "creation_date" : 1563873872,
    "answer_id" : 57160891,
    "question_id" : 3489543,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you are using at least Java 8 you can use method <code>runAsync</code> from class <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/concurrent/CompletableFuture.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">CompletableFuture</a></p>\n\n<pre><code>CompletableFuture.runAsync(() -&gt; {...});\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>If you need to return a result use <code>supplyAsync</code> instead</p>\n\n<pre><code>CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(() -&gt; 1);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
